Niger State Governor, Abubakar Sani Bello, has expressed his heartfelt condolences to the family of Ndanusa Isaiah over the death of Eunice Ndanusa Isaiah, the mother of founder and publisher of Leadership Newspaper, late Sam Nda-Isaiah. Bello in a condolence message described the deceased as a great woman who was able to train children of reputable character among which was the famous late Sam Nda-Isaiah who died on the 11th December, 2020. He said “it is really a difficult and grieving moment for the family members of Ndanusa Isaiah particularly as they buried one of the strong pillars in the family barely a year and three months ago. “We cannot question what God has done but rather, we are to accept his act and pray that God will forgive her all her shortcomings and grant her eternal rest.” The Governor also prayed God to give the family members and well wishers the fortitude to bear the loss.